Jobs Responsibilities
 Reporting to the Nurse Manager, the role is to assist the Nurse Manager/Senior Staff Nurse to supervise and evaluate clinical nursing and administrative activities of the respective area/s designated.
 Help maintain and improve clinical nursing and administrative standards set by SANH (Buangkok) and MOH.
 Provide the full range of nursing care activities in clinical practice and uphold the philosophy and mission of SANH (Buangkok).
 Build teamwork in nursing and with other departments in the holistic care of residents.
 Deputize and assume responsibilities of Nurse Manager/Senior Staff Nurse in his/her absence when the need arises or when assigned.
 Help orientate, supervise and evaluate clinical practice of Senior Enrolled Nurse, Enrolled Nurse, Nursing Aide, Healthcare Assistant and Healthcare Attendant when assigned.
 Participate in evaluation of clinical guidance and in-service programme.
 Help check and execute inventory control.
 Help ensure smooth execution of nursing and administrative policies and procedures set by SANH (Buangkok) .
 Be familiar with code blue, infection control and fire &amp; safety policies of SANH (Baungkok).

Candidate Requirements
Qualification
 Minimum Diploma in Nursing graduate from local Polytechnic Institution.
 Registered with Singapore Nursing Board.
 Minimum of 1 year of related working experience as Staff Nurse.
 Able to work independently and be unfazed with varied requirements of the job.
 Good communication and interpersonal skills.
 Proficiency in Microsoft Excel, Word and PowerPoint.

Core Competencies
 Interested in psychiatric nursing, be caring, matured and current with nursing practices in a community setting.
 Has a heart for social service and will uphold the Home뭩 values/care philosophy.